column1: Table 2. List of all multi-allelic variants (MAVs) and phylogeny-violating variants (MAVs) including those failing downstream filtering

column2: The assigned category of the phylogeny for analysis. In most cases this corresponds to the study ID. However, MPN, CH, ageing and transplant studies are grouped together in the 'Adult_HSPC' category
Sample type undergoing WGS in the phylogeny building studies
Whether the mutation is classified as an MAV or a PVV
For MAVs, this can be simple, removed, or 'FAIL' as defined in the manuscript. For PVVs, this is either 'PASS' or 'FAIL'
The 'mutation reference' for the first mutation that is part of the MAV, or the 'mutation reference' of the PVV. This corresponds to the mutation reference in the read count matrices.
The 'mutation reference' for the second mutation that is part of the MAV; this is not relevant for PVVs. This corresponds to the mutation reference in the read count matrices.
Whether the first mutation is a single nucleotide variant (SNV), multi-nucleotide variant (MNV) or indel
Whether the second mutation is a single nucleotide variant (SNV), multi-nucleotide variant (MNV) or indel. Only relevant for MAVs.
The assigned phylogeny node for each mutation. This corresponds the the node number within the tree object (Newick format)
The node corresponding to the latest ancestor in the phylogeny that the putative lesion is acquired.
The molecular time of the lesion node
The node corresponding to the earliest ancestor in the phylogeny that the putative lesion is repaired.
The molecular time of the lesion repair node
The minimum duration of the lesion, measured in molecular time. In the manuscript this is referred to as the MMLD (minimum molecular lesion duration)

column25: No of cell divisions with lesion
column28: Number of colonies in each wild type clade
column29: Depth in each wild type clade
column36: Number of wild type clades between mutant clades
column38: Reads-based LOH assessment of wild-type clades
column39: ASCAT-based LOH assessment of wild-type clades
column40: Maximum depth of wild-type subclades (PVVs only)
